songs.title: Axl Rose Husband
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
You my Axl Rose husband
Blue hydrangea
White Pontiac heaven
Me, your red, white and blue girl
Star-Spangled danger
You my heavy metal king, king

[Verse 2]
I said, "Daddy, I need you" (Yes)
Greenwich, I need you
Strangled up in ivy
I'm the garden of Eden
Lady Liberty
Teal with flame, I'm shinin'
Queen, queen

[Bridge]
You're my one king, Daddy
I'm your little queen, red, white and blue
You're my one king, Daddy
And I'm your little queen, red, white and blue
White and blue
White and blue
White and blue

[Verse 3]
Record executive
I need you to live, I
Someone come replace you
Should I happen to meet you
Downtown or see you
I would fall down dead
I'm bereaved by you
Bereaved by you

[Verse 4]
In blue denim, I meet you
Barefoot, I need you
Diamond horseshoe sparklin'
You're my king Jewish maven
Kids on vacation
Florida Keys are callin'
"Come back to me"
"Come back to me"
